subSubSection.paragraph:
Amblyseius ( Amblyseius ) stipulatus
.—Ueckermann & Loots, 1988 : 110 .
Euseius stipulatus
.—Moraes et al ., 2004 : 84 ; Chant & McMurtry, 2005 : 216 ; 2007 : 123 .

This species is mainly known from the south of the Western Palearctic region. It is a very common species reported from many plants, including crops such as peach, avocado orchards and vineyards. It is especially abundant in citrus orchards (Ragusa, 1977 ; Ferragut et al ., 1983 ; Papaioannou-Souliotis et al ., 1994 ; Ragusa, 2006 ; Kreiter et al ., 2010 ; Sahraoui et al ., 2012 ). Several studies have shown its ability to feed on pollen but also on pests such as
T . urticae
and
P . citri
(Ferragut et al ., 1992 ; Santaballa et al ., 1994 ; Abad-Moyano et al ., 2009 ; Pina et al ., 2012 ).
Euseius stipulatus
was already found in Morocco by McMurtry & Bounfour ( 1989 ) and Tixier et al . ( 2003 ). With
247 specimens
collected, it was one of the most frequently encountered species.
